The paper discusses reliable storage emulations, which are a fundamental aspect of distributed computing and fall under the category of distributed systems (cs.DC). The paper specifically focuses on the space complexity of multi-writer data stores, which is a topic within distributed storage (cs.DS) and operating systems (cs.OS). The paper also discusses the limitations of read/write operations and the need for more advanced primitives, which is a topic within cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses concurrency and the need for adaptive time complexity, which is a topic within distributed systems and concurrency (cs.Distributed Systems).
